---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<BaseLayout title="About — Nico Abramowski">
  <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-[1fr_320px] items-start">
    <section class="card p-7 reveal">
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">About me</h1>

      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
        I’m Nico, a final-year Computer Science student at the University of Rostock. Most of my hands-on work has been on Linux, networking (TSN/SDN), and scripting. Lately I’ve been focusing on data work—good SQL, tidy models, and small, reliable pipelines.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
        I prefer straightforward solutions: clear dbt models, basic tests that catch the obvious stuff, and dashboards that answer a question without extra clicks. I document as I go and automate repetitive steps.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">Tools I use</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-300">
        <li><strong>SQL:</strong> Postgres, DuckDB; dimensional modeling (Kimball).</li>
        <li><strong>Python:</strong> pandas, basic NumPy; small ETL/ELT scripts.</li>
        <li><strong>Data platform:</strong> dbt, Airflow/Prefect basics, Great Expectations/Soda basics.</li>
        <li><strong>Infra:</strong> Docker, Git, Linux (Mint); some Kafka/Debezium.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">Recent work</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-300">
        <li>Configured Linux hosts for a TSN/SDN testbed and wrote helper scripts.</li>
        <li>Bachelor’s thesis on using large language models for natural-language queries over provenance graphs.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">What I’m looking for</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-300">
        An entry-level role in data warehousing / analytics engineering where I can build and test models, automate ELT, and publish simple, useful dashboards. Remote-friendly is a plus.
      </p>
    </section>

    <aside class="card p-7 reveal" style="transition-delay:.05s">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Contact</h2>
      <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-300">
        <div>Email: <a class="underline" href="mailto:nico.abramowski01@gmail.com">nico.abramowski01@gmail.com</a></div>
        <div>GitHub: <a class="underline" href="https://github.com/Nico-Ab" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Nico-Ab</a></div>
        <div>LinkedIn: <a class="underline" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nico-abramowski-0aa460383" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">nico-abramowski-0aa460383</a></div>
        <div>CV: <a class="underline" href={`${base}CV.pdf`} download>Download PDF</a></div>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
